list.abstract: 《现金》是由Stephen Milburn Anderson执导，肖恩·宾、克里斯·海姆斯沃斯等主演的一部犯罪类型的电影。该片于2010年3月26日在美国上映。 影片讲述了在芝加哥，Sam Phelan和爱妻Leslie在失业后面临支付抵押房贷的困难。开着自己的老别克经过以立交桥时，Sam发现一个皮夹掉下来，打开之后发现内藏60多万美元现金后引发的故事。

yingyinNormal.en: And did you pay cash or credit card? Cash. Always cash. I'm guessing that's not good.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是付现还是刷卡的？我付的现金，从来都是付现，看你们表情，付现不好。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm a little low on cash. How much you got? Nothing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我现金有点紧张啊。你有多少？没有。

yingyinNormal.en: There was an anonymous cash deposit into your savings account yesterday.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有笔匿名现金存款昨天汇入了你的账户。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, he's keys are in the drawer. You know what? I also need some cash.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，他家钥匙放在抽屉里，我还需要一些现金。

yingyinNormal.en: E.N.N. is a huge corporation. They don't pay cash. They'd ask to be billed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 全季新闻网是家大公司。他们不付现金 一定会要求记账。

yingyinNormal.en: Wait here, I'll go pay. I brought some cash. And they'll take an expired Target gift card, right?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你稍等，我去付钱，我带了些钱，他们会收过期的百货现金礼劵，对吧？

yingyinNormal.en: I was raised by two incredible parents, I have a lights out family of my own, and that car you see parked out in front of your house? Cost $143,000 and I bought it for cash. I bought it for cash because I felt like it, and because I can do stuff like that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我被两位非常出色的父母养大，我有自己的幸福家庭，而且，看见停在你家门前的车吗？我花了十四万三千美金，用现金买的。我付现金就因为我高兴，因为我有钱任性。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, why don't I just go down to the food truck and ask them to move? Why are you taking cash? No reason.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这样吧，要不我们下楼去找那小摊请求他们换个地方卖？那你为什么还带上现金了？不为什么。

yingyinNormal.en: Alright, alright, here's the chance. Monica give him cash, Rachel give him your earrings. Something, now, anything.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，好吧，机会来了，莫妮卡，给他现金，瑞秋，把你的耳环给他，快啊，任何东西都给他。

yingyinNormal.en: Trust me, I'm not driving a 7 Series without strippers. No one on the pole has good credit and they're all cash rich.
yingyinNormal.zh: 相信我，没有脱衣舞娘我现在也开不上宝马7系了，脱衣舞娘的信用普遍不高，但是现金充足。

yingyinNormal.en: The sad thing is as we move on to society, when we have less and less cash, and more and more symbolic transactions, credit cards, gift certificates, Paypal and so on.
yingyinNormal.zh: 然而可悲的是，随着我们走向社会当我们越来越少地使用现金，而越来越多地在交易中使用符号货币，如信用卡，礼品券，paypal等等。

yingyinNormal.en: You show them your keyboards, and your monitors. You'll move more inventory that way, and you'll make a hell of a lot more cash. You got me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你也给他们展示键盘、显示器，你让他们在部件清单里随意选择组合这会带给你的商店出乎意料的现金流。你得相信我

yingyinNormal.en: That one. Payment type is cash upon pickup. Who's that for?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个 付款方式是货到付款。看是谁订的东西

yingyinNormal.en: And any extra cash my father has he saves for his yearly trips to Dollywood.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而我爸存的钱用在他每年一次的旅行，桃利屋（性感影星桃利·伯顿建设的主题公园）。

yingyinNormal.en: But you and me, the brokers, we're taking home cold hard cash via commission.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而你我这样的经纪人，我们从佣金里拿的却是真金白银。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh my God. I'm standing at a cash register, holding a credit card, and I'm bored.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我站在收银台，手里拿着信用卡，却觉得很无聊。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, let's get out there and make some money. Cash, cabbage, cheddah-cheeeze!
yingyinNormal.zh: 好的，那我们快出去赚钱吧，有钱有米有面包！

yingyinNormal.en: He wants to cash in, liquidate, take his money and run home. You don't let him do that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他想要套现走人，带着他的钱赶紧回家，你可不能让他这么做。

yingyinNormal.en: Mitchell, what are you doing? I can't cash this. Now, dad, I... You got to sign it first.
yingyinNormal.zh: 米奇尔，你在干什么？这我不能兑现。老爸，我…你得签字啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Ross, we actually watched the documentary together. Ooh. My Chinese food. Let me get my cash.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们是一起看那部纪录片的，我的外卖来了，我去拿钱。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 兑现支票和从发行人的账户中提取资金需要几天的时间。

word_usage.usage:
short作形容词表示“不足；短缺”时，在句中仅作表语，be short of sth.表示“缺……”，如：
I'm short of money right now.
我眼下正缺钱。
